article.headline: Bulldogs to face Hampton in MEAC final
article.linkText: Braddick heats up in second half of Bulldogs' win
article.story:
Semifinal Result
Hampton 73, Howard 64
RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Dustin Braddick scored 14 of his 21 points in the second half and South Carolina State made 22 of 24 second-half free throws Friday to rally past Florida A&M 72-66 in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament semifinals. Braddick scored the first five points during a 10-2 run midway through the half that gave the top-seeded Bulldogs (19-10) a 55-47 lead, and they never trailed again. They will face either Hampton, a 73-64 winner over Howard, for the championship Saturday. Florida A&M (17-12) closed within 62-60 with 1:52 left on a dunk by Jermaine Hill, but Thurman Zimmerman answered with a layup and Clary Judge hit two free throws for South Carolina State. The Bulldogs hit their last 10 free throws in the game. Moses Malone and Zimmerman each added 12 points for the Bulldogs, and Judge had 11. Braddick also led the Bulldogs with nine rebounds and four assists. Demarcus Wilkins led the Rattlers with 16 points, Michael Griffith had 15 and Terrence Woods 14. Hill finished with eight points and 10 rebounds.
